 600:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Bryce\AppData\Local\Temp\ccUevdvu.s 			page 12


 601:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** * \brief
 602:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Sets the state (drive mode and output state) of the port pin used by a sensor.
 603:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  The possible states are GND, Shield, High-Z, Tx or Rx, Sensor. If the sensor
 604:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  specified in the input parameter is a ganged sensor, then the state of all pins
 605:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  associated with the ganged sensor is updated.
 606:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
 607:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** * \details
 608:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  This function sets a specified state for a specified sensor element. For the
 609:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  CSD widgets, sensor element is a sensor ID, for the CSX widgets, it is either
 610:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  an Rx or Tx electrode ID. If the specified sensor is a ganged sensor, then
 611:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  the specified state is set for all the electrodes belong to the sensor.
 612:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  This function must not be called while the Component is in the busy state.
 613:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
 614:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  This function accepts the CapSense_1_SHIELD and
 615:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  CapSense_1_SENSOR states as an input only if there is at least
 616:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  one CSD widget. Similarly, this function accepts the CapSense_1_TX_PIN
 617:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  and CapSense_1_RX_PIN states as an input only if there is at least
 618:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  one CSX widget in the project.
 619:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** 
 620:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Calling this function directly from the application layer is not
 621:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  recommended. This function is used to implement only the custom-specific
 622:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  use cases. Functions that perform a setup and scan of a sensor/widget
 623:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  automatically set the required pin states. They ignore changes
 624:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  in the design made by the CapSense_1_SetPinState() function.
 625:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  This function neither check wdgtIndex nor sensorElement for the correctness.
 626:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
 627:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** * \param widgetId
 628:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Specifies the ID of the widget to change the pin state of the specified
 629:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  sensor.
 630:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  A macro for the widget ID can be found in the CapSense_1 Configuration
 631:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  header file defined as CapSense_1_<WidgetName>_WDGT_ID.
 632:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
 633:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** * \param sensorElement
 634:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Specifies the ID of the sensor element within the widget to change
 635:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  its pin state.
 636:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  For the CSD widgets, sensorElement is the sensor ID and can be found in the
 637:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  CapSense_1 Configuration header file defined as
 638:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  CapSense_1_<WidgetName>_SNS<SensorNumber>_ID.
 639:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  For the CSX widgets, sensorElement is defined either as Rx ID or Tx ID.
 640:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  The first Rx in a widget corresponds to sensorElement = 0, the second
 641:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Rx in a widget corresponds to sensorElement = 1, and so on.
 642:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  The last Tx in a widget corresponds to sensorElement = (RxNum + TxNum).
 643:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Macros for Rx and Tx IDs can be found in the
 644:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  CapSense_1 Configuration header file defined as:
 645:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  - CapSense_1_<WidgetName>_RX<RXNumber>_ID
 646:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  - CapSense_1_<WidgetName>_TX<TXNumber>_ID.
 647:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
 648:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** * \param state
 649:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *  Specifies the state of the sensor to be set:
 650:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *     1. CapSense_1_GROUND - The pin is connected to the ground.
 651:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *     2. CapSense_1_HIGHZ - The drive mode of the pin is set to High-Z
 652:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *        Analog.
 653:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *     3. CapSense_1_SHIELD - The shield signal is routed to the pin
 654:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *        (available only if CSD sensing method with shield electrode is enabled).
 655:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *     4. CapSense_1_SENSOR - The pin is connected to the scanning bus
 656:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *        (available only if CSD sensing method is enabled).
 657:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *     5. CapSense_1_TX_PIN - The Tx signal is routed to the sensor
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Bryce\AppData\Local\Temp\ccUevdvu.s 			page 13


 658:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *        (available only if CSX sensing method is enabled).
 659:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *     6. CapSense_1_RX_PIN - The pin is connected to the scanning bus
 660:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *        (available only if CSX sensing method is enabled).
 661:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *
 662:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** *******************************************************************************/
 663:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Sensing.c **** void CapSense_1_SetPinState(uint32 widgetId, uint32 sensorElement, uint32 state)
